        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 9 at 5:12PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 512 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Three Rivers, moving east at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Three Rivers, Centreville, Colon, Nottawa, Leonidas, Mendon, Burr
Oak, Corey Lake, Wasepi, Clear Lake, Findley, and Fairfax.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM EDT for
southwestern Michigan.</instruction>
